  </div>
</div>

<hr class="featurette-divider">

<div class="text-center my-3">
  <h1>Technologies</h1>
</div>

<div class="container marketing">

  <!-- Three columns of text below the carousel -->
  <div class="row text-center">
    <div class="col-lg-4">
      <%= image_tag "aspnet.png", width: 140, height: 140, class: "rounded-circle mb-2" %>
      <h2 class="fw-normal">ASP.NET Core</h2>
      <p>.NET Core, and especially ASP.NET Core are technologies I'm most familiar with. I'm quite familiar with MVC
        applications, both for server side apps and APIs, and I also have an understanding of Blazor.</p>
      <p>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://github.com/Wikator?tab=repositories&q=&type=&language=c%23&sort=">See more</a>
      </p>
    </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
    <div class="col-lg-4">
      <%= image_tag "rubyonrails.png", width: 140, height: 140, class: "rounded-circle mb-2" %>
      <h2 class="fw-normal">Ruby on Rails</h2>
      <p>A framework I'm constantly learning, mostly for APIs, but for server side apps as well,
        like this one :). Though I have very few completed projects that used this framework, I'm
        very fond of Ruby, and have a basic understanding of Rails.</p>
      <p>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://github.com/Wikator?tab=repositories&q=&type=&language=ruby&sort=">See more</a>
      </p>
    </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
    <div class="col-lg-4">
      <%= image_tag "springboot.png", width: 140, height: 140, class: "rounded-circle mb-2" %>
      <h2 class="fw-normal">Spring Boot</h2>
      <p>Spring boot is a framework I've learned through Hackathon and group projects. I'm
        planning to learn how to use Kotlin instead of Java.</p>
      <p>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://github.com/WIP-Work-In-Progress/wip-platform-be">See more</a>
      </p>
    </div><!-- /.col-lg-4 -->
  </div><!-- /.row -->


  <!-- START THE FEATURETTES -->

  <div class="text-center mt-2">
    <h1>Featured Projects</h1>
  </div>

  <hr class="featurette-divider">

  <div class="row featurette">
    <div class="col-md-7">
      <h2 class="featurette-heading fw-normal lh-1">Movies Service</h2>
      <p class="lead">The biggest project I've made. It uses Neo4J as database, ASP.NET Core as backend,
        and NEXT.js as Frontend. Development took quite a while, because I've learned a great deal
        about non SQL databases, many protocols, including MQTT, SSE etc, and tried to keep code as clean
        as possible, at least on backend.<br />
        <a href="https://moviesservice.onrender.com">Site</a><br />
        <a href="https://github.com/UniversityOfGdanskProjects/projektprogramistyczny-Wikator">Backend</a>

      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5">
      <%= image_tag "moviesservice.png", width: 500, height: 500, class: "img-fluid mx-auto" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="featurette-divider">

  <div class="row featurette">
    <div class="col-md-7 order-md-2">
      <h2 class="featurette-heading fw-normal lh-1">Advent of Code <span class="text-body-secondary">2023</span></h2>
      <p class="lead">In 2023, I took part in Advent of Code. Though I have not completed every single problem,
        I used several different languages, and always tried to make code as readable as possible.<br />
        <a href="https://github.com/Wikator/AdventOfCode2023">Link to repository</a></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5 order-md-1">
      <%= image_tag "adventofcode2023.png", width: 500, height: 500, class: "img-fluid mx-auto" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="featurette-divider">

  <div class="row featurette">
    <div class="col-md-7">
      <h2 class="featurette-heading fw-normal lh-1">Daily Sudoku</h2>
      <p class="lead">Simple full stack application written in Blazor that resulted in me wanting
        to write as fast sudoku solving algorithm as I could. It has few features like new, daily puzzles
        being generated, saving progress, and ability to create and save own puzzle.<br />
        <a href="https://github.com/Wikator/DailySudoku">Link to repository</a>
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5">
      <%= image_tag "dailysudoku.png", width: 500, height: 500, class: "img-fluid mx-auto" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="featurette-divider">

